[SN]TITLE[SN]
South Wales Police continue Pontardawe stabbing probe

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Police are continuing to investigate a serious incident which saw a mother airlifted to hospital after being stabbed and her daughter arrested.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Emergency services were called to a disturbance at Gwyrddgoed Road, Pontardawe, at 17:45 BST on Tuesday.
The 63-year-old victim was taken to hospital where her condition is serious but stable.
Her daughter, 32, is in custody and anyone with information should call South Wales Police on 101.
